## Manual Incident Response

> [!NOTE]
> Use when automated agents are insufficient. See [Endpoint Commands](https://docs.limacharlie.io/8-reference/endpoint-commands/).

### Step 1: Assess

```bash
START=$(date -d '1 hour ago' +%s)
END=$(date +%s)
limacharlie detection list --start $START --end $END --oid {{ org.oid }} --output yaml
```

### Step 2: Isolate if Necessary

```bash
limacharlie sensor isolate --sid <SID> --oid {{ org.oid }}
```

### Step 3: Collect Forensic Data

```bash
# Memory dump (Windows)
limacharlie extension request --name ext-dumper --action dump_memory \
  --data '{"sid":"<SID>"}' --oid {{ org.oid }} --output yaml

# Velociraptor collection
limacharlie extension request --name ext-velociraptor --action collect \
  --data '{"sid":"<SID>","artifact":"<artifact-name>"}' --oid {{ org.oid }} --output yaml
```

### Step 4: Query Historical Events

```bash
limacharlie ai generate-query \
  --prompt "Find all process executions for sensor <SID> in the last 24 hours" \
  --oid {{ org.oid }} --output yaml
```

### Step 5: Document on Case

```bash
limacharlie case add-note --id <case_number> --type remediation \
  --content "Manual response: <describe actions taken>" --oid {{ org.oid }}
```

